    "In particular the condition implies φ(X) ⊂ Y, or said otherwise, that φ is an SC-map (I, X) → (J, Y)Proof.",
    "Put a ∶= ca(I, X) and b ∶= ca(J, Y).",
    "(φ, f) is a B-map if and only if φ ○ π a = π b ○ f. Since π a = i X and π b = i Y, the condition is equivalent to φ(s) = f (s) for all s ∈ X.",
